dct_title_s: Maurice River, Cumberland County, NJ, (Sections No. 1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
dct_description_sm: Section 1 - Maurice River from Wood's Mill Pond in Millville. Map shows the exterior wharf lines established by the Riparian Commission, wharfs, land owners, and soundings.

Section 2 - Shows the Maurice River around the split with Manantico Creek. Map shows the exterior wharf lines, the Maurice River, Buckshutem Creek, and Manantico Creek, soundings, and land owners. Map also uses labels to show upland, meadow, low meadow, high meadow, and swamp.

Section 3 - Maurice River from just north of Port Elizabeth to Mauricetown. Map shows land owners, exterior wharf line, soundings, the Muskee Creek, and the Manamuskin Creek. Places along the River are labeled low meadow, high meadow, upland, and meadow.

Section 4 - Covers area of Maurice River just south of Leesburg to Mauricetown. Map shows the exterior wharf lines, soundings, and wharfs. Mauricetown, Leesburg, and Dorchester are located on the map. The line of meadow, areas of upland, high meadow, meadow, and low meadow are labeled on the map.

Section 5 - Maurice River from Delaware Bay to Port Norris. Map shows the exterior wharf lines, soundings, land owners, grants, and leases. The Bridgeton and Port Norris Railroad, Delaware Bay, and Maurice River Cove are drawn onto the map. There are also areas labeled as high meadows and marsh.
